Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: The forgotten William Le Queux
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00yds45
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 13 May 1988
On hearing of the death of double agent Kim Philby (1912 -1988), Cooke reflects on the influence of forgotten Edwardian spy writer William Le Queux (1864-1927).